## Database — Appwrite collections (database ID: hackfarmer-db)
All documents use Appwrite's camelCase field naming convention.
jobs:           $id, userId, status, inputType, repoName, repoPrivate,
                githubUrl, zipPath, retentionDays, errorMessage,
                $createdAt, completedAt
agent-runs:     $id, jobId, agentName, status, retryCount,
                startedAt, completedAt
user-api-keys:  $id, userId, provider, encryptedKey, isValid, lastUsed
job-events:     $id, jobId, eventType, payload(JSON string), $createdAt

## REST API response field names (snake_case — converted from Appwrite camelCase)
jobs API returns: id, status, input_type, repo_name, repo_private,
                  github_url, zip_path, error_message, created_at, completed_at
agent-runs API:   id, agent_name, status, retry_count, started_at, completed_at, output_summary

Job.status enum:      queued / running / complete / partial / failed
AgentRun.status enum: waiting / running / done / failed
UserApiKey.provider:  gemini / groq / openrouter

## Auth — Appwrite-based
- Frontend: use `account.createOAuth2Session(OAuthProvider.Github, ...)` to sign in
- Frontend session check: `account.get()` on mount (useAuth.js)
- Frontend logout: `account.deleteSession('current')`
- Backend: `get_current_user` dependency reads the Appwrite session cookie (`a_session_*`)
  and calls `Account.get()` via a per-request Appwrite client (build_session_client)
- auth.py router is a stub — GitHub OAuth endpoints and JWT are NOT used

## ProjectState fields — exact names, never add or rename
job_id, user_id, llm (LLMRouter instance),
raw_text, input_type,
project_name, problem_statement, mvp_features, judging_criteria, constraints, domain,
api_contracts (IMMUTABLE after architect sets it),
component_map, tech_stack, database_schema,
generated_files (Annotated[dict[str,str], operator.or_] — merge semantics),
readme_content, pitch_slides, architecture_mermaid,
validation_score, validation_issues,
retry_count, errors, status, github_url

## Realtime event schema — always exactly this shape (written to Appwrite job-events collection)
{
  "eventType": "agent_start|agent_thinking|agent_done|agent_failed|
                job_complete|job_failed|job_queued|heartbeat",
  "payload": "JSON string",
  "jobId": "appwrite-document-id"
}
Frontend subscribes to: databases.{DB_ID}.collections.job-events.documents (Appwrite Realtime)
Every event is written by backend publish() in src/core/events.py — also syncs agent-runs.

## Agent graph topology — fixed, never change
analyst → architect → [frontend_agent + backend_agent + business_agent] (parallel)
→ integrator → validator → conditional:
  score >= 70 OR retry_count >= 3 → github_agent → END
  score < 70 AND retry_count < 3  → integrator (retry_count += 1)

## Immutable rules — never violate, never suggest alternatives
1.  Every agent: async def name(state: ProjectState) -> dict  (return only changed fields)
2.  api_contracts set by architect — zero downstream agents touch it
3.  retry_count checked in graph.py conditional edge only — never inside agent functions
4.  All LLM calls: await state["llm"].complete() — never call providers directly
5.  All prompts: src/llm/prompts/{agent_name}.txt — never hardcode in Python
6.  API keys: retrieved from Appwrite user-api-keys collection, decrypted in the function
    that needs them only — never returned in API responses, never logged
7.  Auth: Appwrite session cookie only — never JWT, never localStorage, never response body
8.  Every agent emits exactly: agent_start → (1+ agent_thinking) → agent_done OR agent_failed
9.  Background tasks: never use request context — pass user_id and job_id explicitly
10. LLMRouter is instantiated per-job with that user's decrypted keys — never a global

## LLM provider configs
gemini:      base_url=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/
             model=gemini-2.0-flash  priority=1
groq:        base_url=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
             model=llama-3.3-70b-versatile  priority=2
openrouter:  base_url=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
             model=meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free  priority=3

## Concurrency model
Global asyncio.Semaphore(3) — max 3 simultaneous pipeline runs across all users.
Per-user: max 1 running job at a time. Additional jobs get status=queued.
Queue check: FastAPI background task polls every 30s, promotes oldest queued job
per user if no running job exists for that user.
No Redis, no Celery — pure asyncio inside the FastAPI process.

## Design system (frontend)
Background:     #0a0a0a
Surface:        #111111
Surface raised: #1a1a1a
Border:         rgba(255,255,255,0.08)
Border hover:   rgba(255,255,255,0.16)
Text primary:   #ffffff
Text secondary: #888888
Accent blue:    #3b82f6
Accent green:   #22c55e
Accent amber:   #f59e0b
Accent red:     #ef4444
Font:           'Space Grotesk' (headings) + 'DM Sans' (body) — Google Fonts
Mono:           'JetBrains Mono' — for all code previews
Animations:     framer-motion, spring physics, never ease-linear for UI elements
Cards:          glassmorphism — bg rgba(255,255,255,0.04), border rgba(255,255,255,0.08)
                backdrop-filter: blur(12px)

## n8n — usage boundaries
ALLOWED:  job completion webhook, file cleanup cron, failed job alert, new user log
FORBIDDEN: never in the critical agent pipeline path, never awaited by FastAPI

